Today, we will learn about epilepsy, a common neurological condition that affects millions of people worldwide.

0:00:06.500,0:00:10.000
What is epilepsy?

0:00:10.500,0:00:18.000
It is a neurological disorder that causes seizures, episodes characterized by abnormal electrical activity in the brain.

0:00:18.500,0:00:24.000
There are various types of seizures.

0:00:24.500,0:00:31.000
Generalized seizures affect both hemispheres of the brain, while focal seizures affect only one part.

0:00:31.500,0:00:40.000
The causes of epilepsy are varied: they may include genetics, trauma, brain infections, or strokes.

0:00:40.500,0:00:49.000
To diagnose epilepsy, studies such as an electroencephalogram are performed.

0:00:49.500,0:00:56.000
Treatments include antiepileptic medications, and in some cases, surgery.

0:00:56.500,0:01:03.000
With appropriate treatment, many people with epilepsy can lead full and active lives.

0:01:03.500,0:01:11.000
If you have epilepsy or know someone who does, remember that support and understanding are essential.

